<title>USA: Standard Federal acquires Curti Insurance.</title>
<headline>Standard Federal acquires Curti Insurance.</headline>
<dateline>TROY, Mich. 1996-09-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Standard Federal Bank said Wednesday it acquired the Curti Insurance Agency Inc of Sterling Heights, Mich.</p>
<p>Under terms of the transaction, the new operation will conduct business as a wholly owned subsidiary of the bank under the name Standard-Curti Insurance Agency Inc.</p>
<p>The Curti Insurance Agency currently collects gross premium revenues of $20 million a year.</p>
<p>	   -- Chicago newsdesk 312 408-8787</p>
